<h1><a name="errata">ERRATA</a></h1>
<p><a href="/docs/Tangram/Storable.html">the Tangram::Storable manpage</a> objects are first encoded with <a href="/docs/MIME/Base64.html">the MIME::Base64 manpage</a>,
because Tangram does not currently have an easy mechanism for calling
<code>DBI-&gt;bind_param()</code> at the appropriate time to flag the column as
binary.</p>
<p><a href="/docs/Tangram/PerlDump.html">the Tangram::PerlDump manpage</a> objects are stored as <code>BYTEA</code> columns, which as
of <a href="/docs/DBD/Pg.html">the DBD::Pg manpage</a> 1.31, also do not get correctly escaped by the DBD
driver.  This also affects the (as-yet not fully functional)
<a href="/docs/Tangram/YAML.html">the Tangram::YAML manpage</a> back-end, which might put <code>\</code> characters into a YAML
document.</p>
<p>It is recommended to use the <code>storable</code> type with <a href="/docs/Tangram/IDBIF.html">the Tangram::IDBIF manpage</a>
for this reason.</p>

